parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The EPB malfunction can cause the vehicle to suddenly stop or lose control, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The EPB engages without warning
the vehicle stops or slows down unexpectedly
the parking brake light illuminates
and the service brake system message appears on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The brake system failure can cause the vehicle to lose braking ability, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The brakes do not engage or respond
the brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the vehicle takes longer to stop
and the "Service Brake System" or "Brake Assist: Alert" message appears on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The ABS system malfunction can cause the vehicle to lose traction or stability, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The ABS system engages unnecessarily
the vehicle pulsates or vibrates when braking
and the "Service ABS System" message appears on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission failure can cause the vehicle to lose power, stall, or become difficult to shift, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle lunges forward upon acceleration
the vehicle starts in park
the vehicle rolls backward without warning
the transmission slips or hesitates
the engine light comes on
the vehicle shakes violently when accelerating
the vehicle stalls
the vehicle will not shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Electronic shifter malfunction can cause the vehicle to roll backward without warning, which can lead to accidents or property damage.
symptoms: The vehicle side mirrors fold inward while driving
the vehicle rolls backward without warning
the vehicle starts in park
the display shows the Buick startup icon after impact.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Clutch and gearbox failure can cause the vehicle to lose power, stall, or become difficult to shift, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the vehicle lunges forward upon acceleration
the vehicle starts in park.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Air conditioning unit failure can cause discomfort and distraction while driving, which can lead to accidents.
symptoms: The air conditioning unit blows hot air only
the vehicle makes a noise that sounds like a hydraulic door hinge.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Fuel system malfunction can cause the vehicle to stall, lose power, or become difficult to start, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle revs to 2-3 RPM when lightly accelerating
the vehicle auto stops and shifts into neutral
the vehicle stalls
the "EVAP LEAK" warning appears.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the automatic start/stop feature can cause the engine to stall or hesitate to start, leading to potential accidents or safety risks, especially when crossing intersections or merging with traffic.
symptoms: Engine shuts down when vehicle stops
hesitation or stalling when accelerating from a stop
transmission light illuminates
engine starts after brake is released.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Bucking and Loss of Acceleration
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine bucking and loss of acceleration can cause the vehicle to stall or roll backwards, increasing the risk of accidents or collisions.
symptoms: Vehicle bucks badly
will not accelerate
rolls backwards
check engine light illuminates
codes P0011
and P0024 set.
